sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K119010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device encodes cI, the protein which controls RcnA. It also contains LuxR, which Induces the expression of cI and aiiA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Osbaldo Resendis, Miguel A. Ramirez, Mariana G. Schiavon, Libertad Pantoja,Martin del castillo Velasco,Mariana B. Reyes, Luis A. Arriola, Daniela Robles, Sur Herrera, Carlos Vargas, Jimena Monzon S, E
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: We based this part in BBa_I729006 from Chiba team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We needed a repressor which could be induced by a "signal" in order to inhibit the RcnA(BBa_K119003, BBa_K119009) activity. We achieved this by taking advantage of the LuxR promoter present in the Chiba device BBa_I729006. So, we placed cI downstream of this promoter and changed the promoter which was controlling aiiA for the LacZ one.
